Sentencas: An analysis is performed on the diffusion of oxygen through tubular porous cathode substrates having several different geometries.
Titulo: Geometry-Dependent Oxygen Diffusion Flux and Limiting Current Density of the Cathode in a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: It is shown that the flux of oxygen as it diffuses through these different substrate geometries can be explicitly expressed by a general analytical form with a unique geometric factor for each type of substrate geometry.
Titulo: Geometry-Dependent Oxygen Diffusion Flux and Limiting Current Density of the Cathode in a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Experimental measurements of the geometry-independent term, oxygen diffusivity, were conducted for two representative geometries: cylindrical and triangular tubes.
Titulo: Geometry-Dependent Oxygen Diffusion Flux and Limiting Current Density of the Cathode in a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: These measurements show good agreement between samples with similar porosities and thus favorably support the oxygen flux equations presented.
Titulo: Geometry-Dependent Oxygen Diffusion Flux and Limiting Current Density of the Cathode in a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Formulations for the limiting current density were also derived directly from the oxygen flux equations.
Titulo: Geometry-Dependent Oxygen Diffusion Flux and Limiting Current Density of the Cathode in a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: These are similarly expressed by a general analytical form with the same unique geometric factor depending on the particular substrate.
Titulo: Geometry-Dependent Oxygen Diffusion Flux and Limiting Current Density of the Cathode in a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Finally, three representative geometries, cylindrical, triangular, and square tubes, are used to illustrate the influence of the various dimensional parameters on the limiting current density.
Titulo: Geometry-Dependent Oxygen Diffusion Flux and Limiting Current Density of the Cathode in a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
